ðŸ”¹ Relational and Logical Operators
2.	Accept three numbers and find the largest using relational and logical operators.
3.	Check if a number is positive, negative, or zero using if-else or ternary operator.
4.	Check if a number is divisible by both 3 and 5.
5.	Accept a year and check whether it is a leap year using logical operators.
________________________________________
ðŸ”¹ Ternary Operator
6.	Find the maximum of two numbers using the ternary operator.
7.	Find the absolute value of a number using a ternary operator.
8.	Accept marks and assign pass/fail using the ternary operator.
________________________________________
ðŸ”¹ Assignment and Compound Operators
9.	Write a program to demonstrate the use of +=, -=, *=, /=, and %= with integer variables.
10.	Demonstrate pre-increment and post-increment operators and print the values before and after.
________________________________________
ðŸ”¹ Bitwise Operators
11.	Write a program to demonstrate bitwise AND, OR, XOR operations.
12.	Find whether a given number is odd or even using bitwise AND operator (&).
13.	Left shift and right shift a number by 2 positions and display the result.
________________________________________
ðŸ”¹ Expression Evaluation
14.	Evaluate and print the result of the following expression:
java
CopyEdit
int result = 10 + 20 * 30 / 5 % 3 - 1;
15.	Rewrite the following if-else as a ternary expression:
java
CopyEdit
if (a > b)
   max = a;
else
   max = b;
________________________________________
ðŸ”¹ Challenge Questions
16.	Accept 5 subject marks, calculate percentage, and print grade using expressions and conditions.
17.	Evaluate the result of a complex expression combining arithmetic, logical, and relational operators.

